        "cooked": "<p>I am familiar with <a href=\"https://community.signalusers.org/t/automatic-censorship-circumvention/12288\" class=\"inline-onebox\">Automatic censorship circumvention</a></p>\n<p>However, I have a lot of friends in a censored country who I am insistently ‚Äúsignal-pilling‚Äù and censorship circumvention DOES NOT kick  in for them automatically, requiring me to brief them on how to find the switch to activate censorship circumvention.</p>\n<p>Also their calls usually remain broken until they activate call relaying.</p>\n<p>After both options are set their Signals usually work normally.</p>\n<p>This may seem like a small issue for technical users but this hugely, massively, painfully complicates onboarding of people who don‚Äôt know much and don‚Äôt like navigating the underbellies of intricate menus, which are regrettably a lot of people.</p>\n<p>Proposed solution:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>make censorship circumvention and call relaying switches ‚Äúfirst class‚Äù part of Signal UI,</li>\n</ol>\n<p>There is more than enough space near the search symbol for 2-3 buttons (Censorship Circumvention, Call Relaying and Proxy Support) near the ‚Äúsearch‚Äù symbol on main signal screen, and it would be an immense pain relief for my humble Signal community onboarding effort.</p>\n<p>Explaining how to  navigate the menu to find relevant switches is a massive source of friction and for some users</p>\n<p>I can spend <strong>up to 40 minutes</strong> just getting some guys to flip two switches so their Signal will start working properly. I would rather say something like ‚Äúsee the button with mask-shaped icon and the arrow-point-arrow button? press them both and try calling me on Signal‚Äù</p>\n<ol start=\"2\">\n<li>make automatic censorship circumvention more aggressive , and also make call relaying activation more aggressive when call misbehavior is detected</li>\n</ol>\n<p>Additionally, given the way where winds are blowing make ‚Äúuse proxy‚Äù a ‚Äúfirst class‚Äù part of Signal UI too (already implied above) so that when the government here will become even more hostile (it will) I can tell people just ‚Äúpress the shield with letter P button‚Äù and start explaining the proxy add menu instead of having them to jump through the ‚ÄúData and Storage‚Äù menu</p>\n<p>P.S.<br>\nIf you think that making these three rather vital features ‚Äúfirst class first screen‚Äù UI elements will overly clutter Signal‚Äôs spartan main screen, at least maybe consider putting them in their own Settings section and call it something like ‚ÄúResilience‚Äù or ‚ÄúPerseverance Features‚Äù or something like that<br>\nAfter all you have Payments surfaced prominently in Settings</p>",
